Susan Monarez was CDC director for under a month, and she displayed admirable integrity in her defense of science-backed policies, including vaccine standards. 

CDC and the nation are worse off without her and the other courageous senior leaders who left the agency yesterday. 

The wrong people are leaving government. 

RFK Jr. is a threat to Americans’ public health and he must resign or be fired for the sake of our country.

https://t.co/cD3H2DuTwu

RFK Jr.’s reckless cuts throughout HHS are gutting the programs and personnel behind America’s health breakthroughs.

As the top Democrat on the Health Subcommittee, I’m sounding the alarm today: RFK Jr.’s agenda is dangerous—and threatens our health, economy, and global leadership in science.

After shady back-room deals, hearings in the dark of night, bullying from the president, and hyper partisanship, House Republicans have forced through Trump’s ‘One, Big Bogus Bill’ that will kick over 13 million Americans off their health care to pay for tax cuts for billionaires.

This bill makes life harder for the American people while enriching the top earners in our country. I voted against this terrible legislation, and I will continue to fight against this extreme and cruel agenda.

Heartbroken to hear about the passing of my friend and colleague, Gerry Connolly. Gerry was a true public servant, always fighting for those he represented and standing up for the issues that impacted his beloved home state of Virginia.

My thoughts are with his wife, Smitty, the entire Connolly family, his staff, and the 11th Congressional district during this sad time.

My thoughts are with President Biden, Dr. Biden and the entire Biden family following the president’s cancer diagnosis.

I know President Biden is a fighter, and I’m praying for his health and a swift recovery.

We’ve been in this markup for nearly 22 hours, and Energy & Commerce Democrats are still going strong as we stand up to Trump’s ‘One Big, Bogus Bill’ that will kick 13.7 million Americans off their health care.

I’m not backing down, and I’ll keep calling out the GOP’s extreme, misguided policies no matter how long we are here.

Let me clear something up.

Cuts to Medicaid through the ‘One Big, Bogus Bill’: 8.6 million to lose health care
Republicans refusing to extend ACA enhanced tax credits: 5.1 million to lose health care

8.6 million + 5.1 million = 13.7 million.

The market is crashing and what is Trump doing? Selling Teslas on the lawn of the White House with his billionaire co-president. 

The corruption is in plain sight.

The behavior of President Trump and Vice President Vance towards President Zelensky is shocking, disrespectful, and un-American.

Ukraine is defending its sovereignty against an aggressive adversary, and the United States must stand with Ukraine against Putin’s illegal invasion.

Unfortunately, the only person happy about how this played out is Putin.
You want to make it harder for people to see their doctors so you can give tax cuts to billionaires.

🚨 Trump's unconstitutional assault on birthright citizenship has been blocked nationwide by a federal judge.

His disdain for the Constitution is being blocked, and we will keep fighting until he backs down.
We cannot allow an unelected billionaire to access this sensitive information, and I will not stand idly by while Trump hands over our government to the wealthiest individuals in our country.

Elon Musk can now access millions of Americans’ Social Security and payment info.

Who does this help? Not the families struggling to put food on the table. https://t.co/AqiDjWkXlM

USAID is critical in advancing U.S. national security interests,  providing humanitarian aid, and strengthening global stability. Musk is an unelected billionaire with no authority to make these decisions.

This isn’t governance, it’s authoritarianism. https://t.co/4dQROm3V3K

The administration never should have issued this freeze in the first place.

The Trump strategy is chaos and confusion, and it is harming every American.

Trump’s action to pause most federal funding plunged our communities in chaos by illegally circumventing Congress’ power of the purse.

The decision by the US District Court to suspend this action is the correct step to keep our communities whole, but it must be made permanent.
Read my statement after the Trump administration froze virtually all federal funding ⬇️ https://t.co/aemhOon1CO

On his first day in office, Trump pardoned hundreds of felons who assaulted Capitol police officers. House Republicans welcome these violent criminals back to our streets.

No one who respects law enforcement can support these outrageous pardons. It's a disgrace.
My statement on today's ceasefire agreement in the Middle East. ⬇️ https://t.co/hqabFsK3Pp

House Republicans just proposed slashing Medicare and Medicaid.

I'll stay in Washington until Hell freezes over to stop them.

I’m on Bluesky! Follow me there to see how I’m working to restore reproductive freedom, end the climate crisis, and improve access to healthcare.

https://t.co/UszGUTnMpb
Vaccines have saved millions of lives around the world, and we need to base our health care policy decisions on science rather than fringe conspiracy theories.

I am deeply concerned about many of RFK Jr.’s health policy views, particularly regarding vaccines & the promotion of unproven treatments. The public servants that he is threatening to fire are the same public servants who led Operation Warp Speed & helped us crush the pandemic.

Today is #WorldDiabetesDay!

Two years ago, I proudly helped pass the Inflation Reduction Act, capping insulin costs at $35 per month for millions of seniors. As Diabetes Caucus co-chair, I will keep working to ensure affordable diabetes care & treatment for every patient.

#TransAwarenessWeek is about ensuring the voices and stories of trans people are heard.

As a founding member of the @EqualityCaucus, I'm working to address the challenges facing the trans community & will fight against efforts to undermine & end nondiscrimination protections.

On Veterans Day, we recognize the bravery of those who have fought for our country. Their dedication has protected our nation and upheld the values we cherish.

To the 31,000 veterans in Denver & the millions more across our nation, thank you for your service. https://t.co/dkqvaK6LxS
There is plenty of serious work for us do—from ensuring that every American can receive the health care they need to building consensus on clean energy solutions.

As the top Democrat on the Energy and Commerce Health Subcommittee, I am committed to improving health care access and affordability as well as enhancing biomedical research to better advance treatments and cures.

I remain focused on this fight and on delivering for the people of Colorado’s First District, regardless of who is in the White House. 
 
Next Congress, I will continue to work in a bipartisan manner on the issues that matter most to my constituents.

The results of the presidential election and Senate races are deeply disturbing, especially for the millions of women whose reproductive rights now hang in the balance. Now more than ever, we need leaders who will stand up for what is right and advocate for the American people.
I am honored to have been reelected by my constituents to continue serving them in the United States House of Representatives.🧵

Your vote is your voice.

Denverites, make sure you head to the polls if you haven’t cast your vote yet and make your voice heard! #ElectionDay2024

It's #NationalDiabetesMonth! As Diabetes Caucus co-chair & a mom to someone with diabetes, I’m working to ensure everyone w/ diabetes can access the care & treatment they need. We must lower insulin costs for ALL Americans & work towards a cure so everyone can live healthy lives.

Once again, we're seeing the devastating impact of Trump's abortion bans. Nevaeh's death isn't an isolated case; it’s part of a growing crisis fueled by the fall of Roe.

Her passing is a heartbreaking reminder of what happens when we deny or delay life-saving care to patients.

Happy Halloween, Denver!

Wishing everyone a fun and safe night.🎃 https://t.co/1pVWhiO24s

Americans shouldn’t have to choose between paying their energy bills or basic necessities.

Thanks to the Biden-Harris Admin, Colorado is the latest state to launch a Home Energy Rebates Program, saving eligible CO residents up to $14K in rebates when making home energy upgrades.

This is the real, deadly impact of abortion bans. No one should have to live in fear of being denied life-saving care.

For Josseli Barnica & the millions of women living under draconian abortion bans nationwide, we can and must do better.

It was great meeting with @UrbanPeakCO leadership & touring The Mothership, their newest facility to support youth experiencing homelessness in Denver.

I look forward to seeing their continued work to create stronger, self-sufficient futures for young people in our community. https://t.co/OVuoVR0Ne2

Glad to see @ENERGY provide a $162.4M loan guarantee to LongPath Technologies to build 1,000+ remote methane monitoring towers.

Thanks to the Biden-Harris Administration, we're closer to achieving our net-zero goals with Colorado leading the charge on climate action.

Great news for Denverites — Thanks to @USDA's Community Food Projects Grant Program, GrowHaus, a nutrition/food justice nonprofit in Denver, will receive $238,000!

I look forward to seeing their continued work to build a healthier, more equitable future for our community.

No one should struggle to afford life-saving medications. @POTUS & @VP are committed to easing this burden.

Proud to support their efforts by helping pass the Inflation Reduction Act, saving Medicare recipients ~$1 billion in out-of-pocket drug costs in the first half of 2024!

Proud to earn a 100% on the @HRC’s 118th Congressional Scorecard. 

Supporting the LGBTQ+ community means fighting for the rights of all people—no matter who they love or how they identify.

Great to meet with the bright young leaders from Girl Scout Troop 68352 and talk about the importance of civic engagement. Proud to see their passion for making a difference right here in Denver! https://t.co/Z2UNFSWLNK

Happy Birthday, @VP! 
 
Thank you for the work you do everyday to make life better for Coloradoans and for hardworking families across the country. https://t.co/TQCRhSsCa6

Don't miss this chance to make sure your coverage fits your needs: https://t.co/IJQpNc4cgd.
Had a great time at the Great American Beer Festival in Denver this weekend! Good to see local Denver and Colorado-based breweries with a strong showing.🍻 https://t.co/RJqeYB1lRJ

Happy Indigenous Peoples’ Day.

Today, we honor the rich histories and cultures of the Indigenous community and reflect on their impact on Colorado and our country. https://t.co/n5jHeisU9P
G'mar Chatima Tovah. To all who observe, I wish you a reflective Yom Kippur.

#WorldMentalHealthDay reminds us that mental health is health.

I’m working in Congress to ensure no one is left behind — whether it's access to services or simply having someone to talk to, every person deserves support.

Amid ongoing relief efforts, I joined @RepMarcyKaptur in urging Speaker Johnson to bring the House back and vote on vital disaster relief funding.
 
This is no time for partisanship—families are counting on us.

Grateful to everyone who joined us today for our Senior Resource Fair in Denver.

A special thanks to the community leaders and organizations who came together to provide valuable resources and support for our seniors. https://t.co/PmFpo8fuxA

@POTUS & @VP are delivering on their promise to families & EJ communities by requiring the replacement of lead pipes within 10 years. Thanks to the Biden-Harris Admin & Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, Denver is on track to remove lead pipes, investing $76M for clean water access.

Georgia residents were on the verge of reclaiming their freedom from a deadly abortion ban—yet the GA Supreme Court put care out of reach once again.

For women like Amber Thurman and Candi Miller, we won’t back down from this fight.

It’s been one year since the horrific attack on Israel by Hamas, taking thousands of innocent lives & shattering families. 

Today, as we remember & honor the victims, we must move towards an end to the conflict & the release of all hostages to secure lasting peace in the region.

The regressive energy policies in Project 2025 would be disastrous for Colorado, raising energy costs by $280 a year & slashing 13.5K jobs. As the top Democrat on the Energy Subcommittee, I'm pushing for smart energy policies to strengthen our economy & bring us into the future.

If MAGA Republicans had their way, they would implement Project 2025, criminalizing abortion nationwide, banning IVF, & taking away birth control access. As @ProChoiceCaucus co-Chair, I'm fighting back—because everyone deserves the freedom to make their own health care decisions.

Shanah Tovah to all those celebrating the new year in Denver!

May this year bring you joy, growth, and renewal.

This is the reality of MAGA's attack on reproductive freedom, delaying life-saving care for patients.

While we mourn the losses of Amber Thurman and Candi Miller, I'm hopeful this decision marks a step toward a future where no one’s rights are denied.

As a @HouseGVP member, I am committed to ending the scourge of gun violence in our country.
